{
  "texts": [
    "LptA was eluted twice (2.5 column volumes of wash buffer supplemented with an additional 180 mM imidazole), concentrated using a 10-kDa-cut-off Amicon centrifugal concentrator (Millipore), flash-frozen and stored at -80 °C until use.",
    "Proteoliposomes were prepared as described previously 59.",
    "Aqueous E. coli polar lipid extract (Avanti Polar Lipids) (30 mg ml -1) and aqueous LPS from E. coli EH100 (Ra mutant; Sigma-Aldrich) (2 mg ml -1) were sonicated briefly for homogenization.",
    "A mixture of 20 mM Tris-HCl (pH 8.0), 150 mM NaCl, 7.5 mg ml -1 E. coli polar lipids, 0.5 mg ml -1 LPS and 0.25% DDM was prepared and kept on ice for 10 min.",
    "Purified Lpt-B 2 FGC was added to a final concentration of 0.86 μM, and the mixture was left on ice for 20 min."
  ]
}